# Naming Conventions

Follow these conventions for all new and renamed files and constants.

## Pages, Layouts & Components (`.tsx`)

- **Convention:** PascalCase
- **Examples:** `LoginPage.tsx`, `BrandLayout.tsx`, `AppSidebar.tsx`, `RejectApplicationModal.tsx`, `RootLayout.tsx`
- **Exception:** Do not rename files under `src/components/ui/` — they follow shadcn’s default (e.g. `button.tsx`, `dropdown-menu.tsx`). New components outside `components/ui` use PascalCase.

## Hooks (custom hooks & TanStack Query hooks)

### App / UI hooks

- **File name:** kebab-case after the `use-` prefix: `use-<name>.ts`
- **Examples:** `use-mock-data.ts`, `use-auth.ts`
- **Location:** `src/lib/hooks/`

### API query hooks (`src/api/queries/`)

| Scope | Folder | File name | Exported hook (examples) |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Shared** (auth, utilities) | `queries/` root | `use-<feature>.ts` | `useAuthSync`, `useAuthMe` |
| **Clipper** | `queries/clipper/` | `use-<feature>.ts` | `useClipperDashboard` (from `use-dashboard.ts`) |
| **Brand** | `queries/brand/` | `use-<feature>.ts` | `useBrandDashboard` (from `use-dashboard.ts`) |

Rules:

- **File name:** always `use-<kebab-case-feature>.ts` (e.g. `use-dashboard.ts`, `use-auth.ts`). Do **not** repeat the role in the file name when the file already lives under `clipper/` or `brand/`.
- **Exported hook:** camelCase, `use` prefix. Include **role** in the hook name when it is role-specific (`useClipperDashboard`, `useBrandCampaigns`) so call sites stay explicit.
- Do **not** suffix with the underlying TanStack API (`Mutation`, `Query`) — name by intent (`useAuthSync`, not `useAuthSyncMutation`).

## API services (`src/api/services/`)

| Scope | Example path | File name |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Shared | `services/auth.ts`, `services/campaigns.ts` | `<domain>.ts` or existing name |
| Clipper | `services/clipper/dashboard.ts` | kebab-case or short domain: `dashboard.ts`, `submissions.ts` |
| Brand | `services/brand/dashboard.ts` | same as clipper |

- **Functions:** `camelCase` — `getClipperDashboard`, `postAuthSync`.
- Do **not** prefix the filename with `clipper-` or `brand-` when it already sits under `clipper/` or `brand/`.

## API types (`src/api/types/`)

| Scope | Example path |
| --- | --- |
| Shared | `types/global.types.ts`, `types/auth.types.ts`, `types/campaign.types.ts` |
| Clipper | `types/clipper/dashboard.types.ts` |
| Brand | `types/brand/profile.types.ts` |

- **File name:** `<feature>.types.ts` (kebab-case or camelCase **feature** segment; be consistent with existing files in the same folder).
- **Type names:** PascalCase — `ClipperDashboardData`, `AuthMeData`.

## Type-only modules (non-API)

- **File name:** `<name>.types.ts`
- **Location:** e.g. colocated types elsewhere — follow the same `*.types.ts` pattern.

## Utility & Logic Files (`.ts`)

- **Convention:** camelCase
- **Examples:** `mockData.ts`, `walletAddress.ts`, `paymentMethodIcons.ts`, `authStore.ts`
- **Applies to:** utils (under `src/lib/utils/`: e.g. `cn.ts`, `currency.ts`, `date.ts`, `displayName.ts`, `isLikelyHttpUrl.ts`), stores, validations (under `src/lib/validations/`), constants (under `src/lib/constants/`: e.g. `paymentMethodIcons.ts`), domain helper folders (e.g. **`src/lib/campaigns/`** — camelCase filenames like `createCampaignPayload.ts`), and other non-component modules (excluding hooks and `*.types.ts` files above)

## Providers (React context / app wrappers)

- **Location:** `src/providers/` (e.g. auth, wallet) or `src/lib/providers/` (e.g. TanStack Query)
- **Convention:** PascalCase for component files (e.g. `AuthProvider.tsx`, `QueryProvider.tsx`)

## Constants

- **In code:** UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g. `MAX_RETRIES`, `DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE`)
- **Location:** Constant data and config live under `src/lib/constants/` (e.g. `paymentMethodIcons.ts`); file names stay camelCase

## Route guards / layout-level components

- **Location:** `src/components/guards/` (e.g. `ProtectedRoute.tsx` — use `index`, `guestOnly`, or `requiredRole` props).

## Page structure (colocate page-specific components)

- Prefer **page folder + index**: `pages/<role>/<PageName>/index.tsx` plus any page-specific components in the same folder (e.g. `ApplicationStatusBadge.tsx`, `RejectApplicationModal.tsx` inside `pages/brand/ApplicationsPage/`). This avoids putting page-only components in `src/components/`.
- **One folder per URL area** when routes share a base path — do not split list vs detail vs modals into sibling folders (`campaign-details/`, `create-campaign/`, …) for the same feature.
  - **Brand** — **`pages/brand/campaigns/`**: `CampaignsPage.tsx`, `CreateCampaignPage.tsx`, `CampaignDetailPage.tsx`, page-specific pieces colocated in the same folder where practical.
  - **Clipper** — **`pages/clipper/campaigns/`**: `CampaignsPage.tsx`, `CampaignDetailPage.tsx`, colocated pieces (`SubmitReportModal.tsx`, `ShareCampaignModal.tsx`, …). Same pattern: one folder per `/campaigns` route tree.
- **Page-only helpers** — Pure functions that are **not** reused elsewhere (and are unlikely to be) may stay in the page file. Put them **below** the default-exported page component, using `function helperName() { ... }` so hoisting stays safe. Types used only by that page usually sit **above** the component. Logic that is **reusable** across routes or roles belongs under **`src/lib/campaigns/`** (or another domain folder under `src/lib/`); **prefer extending an existing related file** (e.g. `createCampaignPayload.ts`, `createCampaignFormHelpers.ts`, `createCampaignPayoutTiers.ts`) before adding a new `lib/campaigns/*.ts` module.

## Folders

- Use **lowercase** for single words: `brand`, `clipper`, `utils`, `hooks`
- Use **kebab-case** for multi-word folders: `payment-methods`, `mock-data` (optional; lowercase is also acceptable)
- Under `src/api/`, use fixed segments **`clipper`** and **`brand`** (not `clippers` / `brands`).

## Assets (images, icons, SVGs)

- **Convention:** kebab-case
- **Examples:** `security-bank.svg`, `bdo.svg`, `maribank.png`
- **Applies to:** Files under `assets/` (e.g. `assets/banks/`, `assets/crypto/`, `assets/devices/`, `assets/e-wallets/`)

## Quick Reference

| Type | Convention | Example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Page / layout / component (`.tsx`, except `components/ui`) | PascalCase | `CampaignsPage.tsx` |
| API query file (shared) | `use-<kebab>.ts` at `api/queries/` | `use-auth.ts` |
| API query file (clipper/brand) | `use-<kebab>.ts` under `api/queries/clipper/` or `brand/` | `clipper/use-dashboard.ts` |
| API service (clipper/brand) | `<domain>.ts` under `api/services/clipper/` | `clipper/dashboard.ts` |
| API types (clipper/brand) | `<feature>.types.ts` under `api/types/clipper/` | `clipper/dashboard.types.ts` |
| Hook files (app, `lib/hooks`) | `use-<kebab>.ts` | `use-auth.ts` |
| Type modules | `<name>.types.ts` | `auth.types.ts` |
| Utility / logic (`.ts`) | camelCase | `mockData.ts` |
| Domain helpers (`lib/campaigns/`, etc.) | camelCase | `createCampaignPayload.ts` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_RETRIES` |
| Folders | lowercase / kebab-case | `brand`, `clipper` |
| Assets (images, icons) | kebab-case | `security-bank.svg` |
